      <h1><a href="https://grafana.github.io/helm-charts/">helm-charts</a></h1>
      

      <h1 id="grafana-community-kubernetes-helm-charts">Grafana Community Kubernetes Helm Charts</h1>

<p><a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache%202.0-blue.svg" alt="License" /></a>
<a href="https://artifacthub.io/packages/search?repo=grafana"><img src="https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https://artifacthub.io/badge/repository/grafana" alt="Artifact HUB" /></a></p>

<p>The code is provided as-is with no warranties.</p>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p><a href="https://helm.sh">Helm</a> must be installed to use the charts.
Please refer to Helm’s <a href="https://helm.sh/docs/">documentation</a> to get started.</p>

<p>Once Helm is set up properly, add the repo as follows:</p>

<div class="language-console highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="go">helm repo add grafana https://grafana.github.io/helm-charts
</span></code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can then run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">helm search repo grafana</code> to see the charts.</p>

<!-- Keep full URL links to repo files because this README syncs from main to gh-pages.  -->
<p>Chart documentation is available in <a href="https://github.com/grafana/helm-charts/blob/main/charts/grafana/README.md">grafana directory</a>.</p>

<h2 id="contributing">Contributing</h2>

<!-- Keep full URL links to repo files because this README syncs from main to gh-pages.  -->
